'''Africa Today TV (ATTV)''' is an independent public service and educational channel for the American and African audience that is interested in African & International affairs.
== History == The channel was launched on 5th August, 2014 on [[MHz Networks]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.mhznetworks.org/about/press/africa-today-tv-launches-mhz-networks|title=Africa Today TV Launches on MHz Networks|date=2014-08-06|work=MHz Networks: Programming for a Globally Minded Audience|access-date=2017-07-06|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170821002352/http://www.mhznetworks.org/about/press/africa-today-tv-launches-mhz-networks|archive-date=2017-08-21|dead-url=yes|df=}}</ref> The Channel is available on [[Comcast]] 275, [[Cox Communications|Cox]] 470, [[RCN Corporation|RCN]] 30, [[Verizon Fios|Verizon FioS]] 457, [[Dish Network]] 8077 and [[DirecTV]] 56/2183. ATTV started streaming live on their website from April 2016.
== Current Shows == [[Carol Pineau]] is currently hosting a talk show titled "'''Africa and The Trump Administration'''" which airs on '''[http://africatodaytv.com/africaandtrump/ Africa Today TV]''' where she discusses and debates with a panel of experts on the evolving US Africa relationship from both African and American perspectives.
